args: Prince Alfonse? What are you doing?
Writing up all we have discovered\nin our investigation thus far.
Dude, that is a LOT of writing.\nI'm getting dizzy...just...reading...\nUuuurgh...
Thanks for catching me before I ended\nup as a floor pancake.
Actually, I am a prince by the basic\ndefinition of the word—the prince of Askr.
No duh, Captain Literal. I'm just saying\nthat you also act the part.
You're smart and tough and cool and stuff.\nYou're not really like our prince at all.
Still your tongue, Notte! His Highness\nis a wonderful individual!
Easy there, girl! I'm not talkin' smack!\nIt's just that Alfonse seems more...\nyou know? Regal and junk.
I suppose His Highness IS unusually\npersonable for royalty.
Right? He's more like a regular dude.\nHe even got scolded for sneaking off to go\nfor a walk about town! Ha ha ha!
But that's a good thing, because it lets him\nunderstand how us common peasants feel.
I'm not certain I'd call myself a peasant,\nbut we are all proud of His Highness.
He must be honored to be spoken\nof so highly by his vassals.
He seems an upstanding individual—\nboth as a man and a ruler.
*pant* *pant* All right, I think that's\nenough training for today.
That was quite the display\nof swordsmanship.
I didn't notice you there, Prince Alfonse.
That is concerning. Training is important,\nbut so is being aware of your surroundings.\nYou are in charge of this castle, after all.
Though it seems that relaxed nature\nis part of the reason your people\nhold you in such esteem.
I was speaking of you with some of your\nvassals today; it is clear how much\nthey all admire you.
Well, I'm glad to hear that—but I still\nhave a lot of room for improvement.
I don't have the aura of a prince in\nthe way that you do, for example.
Everyone describes me that way,\nbut I'm not certain I fit the mold\nof a typical highborn noble.
You certainly seem that way to me.
Hmm... I've not yet spoken to you\nabout the Order, have I?
The Order of Heroes is a group that\nfights to protect the peace of Askr.
I was determined to join, and so I did.
I'm surprised the people around you were\nokay with that.

Oh, I met resistance—from my father in
particular. But this was simply something
that mattered to me more than having
everyone's approval.
I know exactly how you feel.
I imagine you must, seeing as you're\na prince who fights on the front lines.
Heh. Perhaps we're more similar\nthan I first imagined.
Quite. In fact, just speaking with you\nreminds me of an old friend back in Askr.\n...I miss him terribly.
I hope you can find your way home\nand see him again soon.
Alas, even if I do find a way home,\nI fear that will never happen.
He is a former member of the Order,\nand a very close friend.
But...his situation is complicated.\nHe could stay with us no longer.
No matter how far apart we are,\nI'll never forget him—in that way,\nwe will always remain connected.
But the more you value someone...
...the more it hurts when you lose them.\nHaving suffered terrible losses myself,\nI know well the truth of that statement.
Losing my family was the worst pain I've\never experienced, but I'd still take it\nover never having known them at all.
I imagine you feel the same\nabout your former friend.
Bonds of friendship aren't things to be\ncast aside easily once they're forged.
The two of us are from different worlds,\nso the time will eventually come\nwhen we have to part.
But I can't help but feel I'd be happy\nto call myself your friend.
